description: Deterministic Logarithmic-space is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a deterministic Turing machine, using only a logarithmic amount of writable memory space.
Nondeterministic Logarithmic-space is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a nondeterministic Turing machine, using only a logarithmic amount of writable memory space.
Deterministic Polynomial Time is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a deterministic Turing machine in a polyomial amount of computation time.

Bounded-error Probabilistic Polynomial Time is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a probalistic Turing machine in a polyomial amount of computation time with an error probability bounded by 1/3.
Zero-error Probabilistic Polynomial Time is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a probalistic Turing machine in a polyomial amount of computation time without error.

Randomized Probabilistic Polynomial Time is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a probalistic Turing machine in a polyomial amount of computation time with 1-sided bounded error.

Nodeterministic Polynomial Time is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a nondeterministic Turing machine in a polyomial amount of computation time. It is also defined as the complexity class of decision problems that can be verified by a deterministic Turing machine in a polynomial amount of computation time.
Deterministic Polynomial-space is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a deterministic Turing machine, using only a polynomial amount of writable memory space.
Deterministic Exponential Time is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a deterministic Turing machine in an exponential amount of computation time.
Nondeterministic Exponential Time is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a nondeterministic Turing machine in an exponential amount of computation time.
Deterministic Exponential-space is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a deterministic Turing machine, using only an exponential amount of writable memory space.
Nondeterministic Exponential-space is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a nondeterministic Turing machine, using only an exponential amount of writable memory space.
Nick's Class is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a parallel computer with a polynomial number of processors in a polylogarithmic amount of computation time.
NC^1 is the complexity class of decision problems that can be solved by a parallel computer with a polynomial number of processors in a O((log n)^1) amount of computation time.
